abstract: The Chicago papers bring news of the death, in that city, of Mr. JAMES G. BURNETT. Mr. BURNETT was born in Edinburgh, in Scotland, in 1819. Having served an apprenticeship as a printer in his native town, he came to the United States when in his fifteenth year, and for some months earned a livelihood as a compositor. Circumstances, of which no record exists, led him to enter the ranks of the dramatic profession.

abstract: JOSEPH NESBITT, was arrested in Newark last evening for shooting his wife. He has been married about eighteen months to a young lady whose acquaintance he made in Newark.
